Effective Date: February 8 2026
Overview
My Time Matters respects your privacy and is designed to function without collecting, storing, or transmitting personal data.
Your information stays on your device and under your control.

Information Collection
My Time Matters does not collect any personal data.
Specifically:
No accounts or logins are required
No personal identifiers are collected
No analytics or usage tracking is used
No location data is collected
No data is transmitted to external servers
All information entered into the app is stored locally on your device only.

Data Usage
Because no data is collected, no data is used, shared, sold, or analyzed.

Third-Party Services
My Time Matters does not use third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking services.
If you choose to purchase a subscription or upgrade, payments are handled securely by Apple’s App Store. My Time Matter does not receive or store payment information.

Data Storage & Deletion
All app data is stored locally on your device.
Deleting the app removes all associated data.

Children’s Privacy
My Time Matters does not knowingly collect data from children under the age of 13. Since no data is collected, compliance with children’s privacy regulations is inherently maintained.

Legal Disclaimer
My Time Matters is provided for informational and personal tracking purposes only.
The app does not provide legal, financial, tax, or employment advice. All calculations are estimates based on user-entered information and may not reflect employer-specific policies, contracts, or applicable laws.
Users are responsible for how they interpret and use the information provided by the app. For employment, compensation, or legal decisions, users should consult a qualified professional.
Changes to This Policy
If My Time Matter’s data practices or functionality change, this Privacy Policy will be updated accordingly. Any changes will be reflected by an updated effective date.


